    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is offset by the strong experimental sample size (N=11), dual-laboratory confirmation, and conservative acceptance bounds. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework accurately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
